commit.message: Refresh man page

Add a warning when failing to drop DRM master

When running radeontop as normal user from the console, DRM master
cannot be dropped. On a VT switch, other clients (eg. X11) are not
able to regain master and crash or exit. Users of systemd-logind
should not be affected.
Add support to open DRM device nodes by pathname

Rework of DRM initialization code

Added return value and error checking to init_drm(). DRM version is
passed as argument to init_radeon(). Redundant message removed, as
amdgpu_device_initialize() always print an error message. Moved
drmDropMaster() to authenticate_drm(), as required only if master.

Add support to discover devices via DRM

Added find_drm() to discover devices via drmGetDevices(), like the
original finddrm() but with OpenBSD and DragonFly support too. It
should help with issues #36, #48 and #72.

Older find_pci() is used as fallback method.
Move libdrm code to separate functions
Warning fix, make the struct copy explicit

Move pciaccess code to separate functions

findGPUDevice() renamed to find_pci() and the pci_dev parameter is
added. The resulting pci_device is no more returned as a pointer to
pciaccess allocated memory, instead it is copied to caller allocated
pci_dev, allowing pciaccess init and cleanup within the function.
Restore libdrm defines, so the non-root-radeon support works on older libdrm but new kernel
Warning fix, clarify two radeon error messages
Update man page

Fix matching PCI bus 0 via command line argument

When running with -b0 command line and the first valid card is not on
bus 0, it opens the first card instead to show the error message.
